'''Kelly Druyts''' (born 21 November 1989) is a Belgian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]], who currently rides for [[UCI Women's Team]] {{ct|DVE2}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrouwenpeloton.be/home/2018/12/22/doltcini-van-eyck-met-belgische-en-franse-aanwinsten-naar-2019|title=Doltcini-Van Eyck met Belgische en Franse aanwinsten naar 2019|language=Dutch|trans-title=Doltcini-Van Eyck with Belgian and French acquisitions for 2019|date=22 December 2018|accessdate=10 February 2019|work=Vrouwenpeloton.be|publisher=Vrouwenpeloton}}</ref> She finished in second place in the [[Belgian National Road Race Championships]] in 2010.<ref name="CyclingArchives">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=21121 |title=Kelly Druyts |accessdate=4 May 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref> She won a bronze medal in [[2012 UCI Track Cycling World Championships – Women's scratch|the scratch race at the 2012 UCI Track Cycling World Championships]], and gold in [[2014 UCI Track Cycling World Championships – Women's scratch|the scratch race at the 2014 Championships]].

Druyts is from a sporting family: her father, Ronny, played youth football with [[Beerschot AC]] and at the senior level with Dynamo Niel, where he was a champion in the [[Belgian Provincial leagues]], her sister Steffy was a multiple national champion in gymnastics, and she is the sister of racing cyclists [[Jessy Druyts]], [[Demmy Druyts]], [[Lenny Druyts]] and [[Gerry Druyts]]. Kelly was a national champion in [[triathlon]] and [[duathlon]] before focussing on cycling.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20150503_01661072 |title=De koersmama deel 1: Hoe groei je uit tot een wielerfamilie? |last=Lemmens |first=Karel|date=4 May 2015|website=[[Het Nieuwsblad]]|language=Dutch|trans-title=The race mama part 1: How do you grow a cycling family? |access-date=27 May 2016}}</ref>

